citations.narrative:
A complete physical exam of the 16 adult dogs is overdue according to the Program of Veterinary Care. The last physical
exam was completed on July 12, 2024. To help ensure that the adequate veterinary care is being provided/maintained for
the dogs and that the program of veterinary care is being followed, annual exams must be conducted at least once every
12 months. Licensee must ensure that all adult dogs have a physical exam conducted by a veterinarian at least once
every 12 months.
• To be corrected by: September 17, 2025
This inspection and exit interview were conducted with licensee.
